  "texts": [
    "The MLP predicts the phase distribution ϕ, the three components of the dimensionless velocity vector u * = (u *, v *, w *) T, and the dimensionless pressure p * at the spatio-temporal coordinates (x *, y *, z *, t *).",
    "The loss function L comprises data loss terms L Data for ϕ, u *, and p *, as well as physics-informed loss terms.",
    "The physics-informed loss terms enforce the governing equations and are defined as the MSE of the following residuals: L Conti, enforcing the continuity equation; L Adv, representing the advection equation for phase distribution ϕ, and L NSE, j, representing the Navier-Stokes equations for momentum conservation, with j = (x, y, z) indicating the spatial components.",
    "The weights θ of the joint neural networks are updated by minimizing the composite loss L(θ, x, t) representing the weighted sum of the physics-informed and data loss terms.",
    "Figure S3:S3Figure S3: Evolution of the loss terms during training of PF-VcPINNs optimized for velocity and pressure inference."
